# Design Plan

You are drafting the design plan for the next phase of {{ project_name }}. The autonomous builder normally runs this, but you can invoke it manually from any stage.

## Required reads

- [Workflow state](../../roadmap/state.md) — parse `Phase`, `Stage`, open slice evidence
- [Vision lock](../../docs/vision/VISION-LOCK.md) — authoritative scope
- [Roadmap](../../roadmap/README.md)
- [Open questions](../../docs/reference/open-questions.md) — flag blockers
- [ADR index](../../docs/architecture/decisions/README.md)

## Input

Phase description: **${input:phaseDescription}**

## Task

Write `roadmap/phases/phase-N-design.md` (where `N` = next phase from CURRENT-STATE). The file **must** contain every section below, in this order.

### Required structure

```markdown
# Phase N: <Title>

## Status
draft | in-critique | approved | waived

## Goal
One paragraph: what this phase delivers and why.

## User Stories
_(populated by product-owner handoff; leave as `(to be populated by product-owner)` if not yet invoked)_

- **As a** <user> **I want to** <capability> **so that** <outcome>.

## Acceptance Criteria
Measurable outcomes per story.
- [ ] Criterion 1 (observable, verifiable)
- [ ] Criterion 2

## Non-Goals
Explicit exclusions to prevent scope creep.
- Not doing X because Y.

## Risks
- **Risk**: description — **Mitigation**: approach.

## ADR Candidates
Decisions in this phase that warrant capture in `docs/architecture/decisions/`.
- ADR-NNN (proposed): <decision title> — captures choice between A vs B.

## Test Strategy
Map each acceptance criterion to a test layer.
- Unit: ...
- Integration: ...
- End-to-end: ...
- Manual: ...

## Slice Breakdown
Ordered, independently-shippable slices with file-level hints.
1. **Slice 1 — <name>**: files touched, scope, tests to write.
2. **Slice 2 — <name>**: ...
```

## After writing

Direct edits to `roadmap/state.md` are blocked by `tool-guardrails.py`. Stamp the planning fields via the sanctioned helper:

```bash
python3 .github/hooks/scripts/write-plan-evidence.py design-plan roadmap/phases/phase-N-design.md
python3 .github/hooks/scripts/write-plan-evidence.py design-status draft
```

The helper validates that the plan file exists and that the status value is in the canonical vocabulary (`draft | in-critique | approved | revise | rethink | waived`).

## Handoff

When the draft is complete, hand off to:

- **product-owner** — to populate the User Stories section.
- **critic** — for adversarial review (only after product-owner if applicable).

> **If you are the planner subagent dispatched by `autonomous-builder`, skip this section.** Nested subagent invocation is disabled by default (`chat.subagents.allowInvocationsFromSubagents`), and the builder owns the `planning → design-critique` transition explicitly. The builder will dispatch product-owner and critic itself once it sees `Design Status: draft`. Act on the Handoff section only when a human invoked you directly via `/design-plan`.

## Rules

- Do **not** make implementation decisions here — that's `/implementation-plan`.
- Flag unresolved blockers in `docs/reference/open-questions.md`; do not paper over them.
- Do not edit source code. Your scope is plan files + `state.md`.
- Respect authority order: VISION-LOCK > ADRs > architecture > roadmap. If this phase would contradict a higher doc, raise it instead of silently working around it.
